<p class="mt-8">
    FoundersPC data is available through a REST API; typically on a licensed or partnership
    basis.
    <a href="mailto:jeff@gmail.com" class="btn btn-neon p-1 m-0 text-decoration-underline">
        Contact us
    </a>
    for more information - include a brief description of what you're building.
</p>
<h2>Access &amp; Authentication</h2>
<p>
    URL:
    <a class="p-1 text-decoration-underline text-info" href="https://founderspc.com/api/">
        https://founderspc.com/api/
    </a>
    <br>Include your key in a request header:
    <span class="text-decoration-underline text-info">
        HARDWARE-API-TOKEN : [your-api-access-token]
    </span>
</p>
<h2>Rate Limit</h2>
<p>
    Endpoints are rate limited. The specific limit varies
    <span class='bg-secondary'>
        (1 request in 1 minute)
    </span>. If you are seeing
    <span class="bg-danger">
        429 Too Many Requests
    </span>
    , contact us to discuss your needs.
</p>
<h2>Data Format</h2>
<p>
    Our API conforms to the
    <a href="http://jsonapi.org/" class="btn btn-neon p-1 m-0 text-decoration-underline">
        JSON API
    </a>
    specification.
    This spec defines conventions to nicely model different data types, their relationships, and
    metadata. There's likely a
    <a href="http://jsonapi.org/implementations/"
        class="btn btn-neon p-1 m-0 text-decoration-underline">
        JSON API client
    </a>
    in your
    language.
</p>
